issue.title: Eager mode generator improvements for multiple onnx operators and extra test cases

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: Improve generator to include line numbers for ORT error messages, isolate variable names per operator, add some test cases for an existing function.

**Motivation and Context**
- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve?
Generator support for nested/multi Onnx operators per Aten operator needed strengthening to allow input variable reuse (e.g. if two different onnx operators in the same generated aten operator implementation used the same variable, say "self", two lines like `auto ort_input_self = create_ort_value(invoker, self);` would be added to the same function and cause compile time failure.), node attributes re-use, and debugging improvement (the generic "ORT return failure" text is repeated for each Onnx operator invocation, so without line numbers the user cannot easily tell which invocation generated the failure).

Adding test cases for masked_select and an implementation based on Onnx operators instead of torch fallback, including validating broadcast support.

- If it fixes an open issue, please link to the issue here.

issue.title: Eager mode generator support non-tensor return types

labels.name: api
labels.description: issues related to all other APIs: C, C++, Python, etc.

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
aten::equal has been handwritten for eager mode. It can almost be generated by specifying the following in atenops.py:
`"aten::equal": Not(ReduceMin(Cast(Equal("self", "other"), 6), keepdims=0))`

**Describe the solution you'd like**
The generator can create the code from the mapping or similar mapping listed above.

However, this fails  because the return type is a bool type (not a tensor)

If the generator can be modified to handle this then the handwritten code can be removed.

Note: I have not measured the impact on making these changes for supporting other aten->onnx ops mapping so reward for these changes should be measured before investing.

Related issue: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/12055

Related code changes:
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/12020
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/pull/12111
